<br>
I find the lack of action from Mythic unnerving.  I find that the realm that I PAY to play in is obviously not getting the same consideration as the others.  This isn't rocket science nor does it take me 1 year of playing time to show concrete evidence of this. 9 servers are now offering /level 30's to Midgard in order to balance the populations on these servers.  I'd like to say this is a clear indication that mythic has failed in it's ability to respond to it's customers demands.  <br>
<br>
Over the last 6 months in this game, mythic has appeared to really focus diminishing it's least popular realm (the oft spoken LA nerf, recent savage fixes, and the skalds still looking for a definition).  It seems evident that the most simple measure to both draw people back to midgard and to address imbalance issues would be to introduce a new class or two.  A relative easy fix and should inspire a new exploration of this realm.  Mythic needs to inject more interest and fun to this realm, for it is failing and it's plain to see.  <br>
<br>
HOWEVER...this may be because I am on a bad server for mid, but am I way off?<br>
<br>
<br>
Armalldin 50 Skald Guin<br>
Dhanzer 46 Shaman Guin<br>
