<br>
I'd like to assume that Mythic arre working on some uber RvR balance plan for the upcoming RvR patch, and they have a seperate team working 24/7 on that, regardless of other patches/expansions.<br>
<br>
However, what I really hate about Mythic, and think it's their worst mistake as a company, is NOT BEING CLEAR on any of their future plans, not dispensing any information about balancing to their customers (for the sole purpose of reducing frustration) and leaving the people with a feeling they're fighting windmills.<br>
<br>
All I know for now, is that there will be an RvR expansion/patch somewhere in 2004, but I haven't the slightest about what's going to be there. I mean, how hard is to throw a word occasionally, saying something like &quot;Skald RA list and balance are being looked at, but the major changes will be released with the PvP expansion. However, slight changes may be released earlier if they don't unbalance the main PvP expansion plans we're working on currently&quot;?<br>
<br>
I personally don't care if a few whiners leave, but people are closing accounts or rerolling other realm due to the fact they can't see any light at the end of the tunnel.<br>
